explanation:
- UtAssert_Compare_t: The enum/type definition is required to know the set of valid values, their underlying integer representations and whether additional enumerators exist. This determines whether every possible enum value is covered by the switch (so the default case would be unreachable) or not.
- UtAssert_Compare_* enumerators (EQ, NEQ, LT, GT, LTEQ, GTEQ, BITMASK_SET, BITMASK_UNSET): The concrete enumerator definitions and their assigned integer values are needed to check whether the switch cases in UtAssert_GetOpText cover all distinct enumerators, and to detect any duplicate values (which can make some case labels or the default unreachable).
- UtAssert_GenericIntegerCompare: This caller is required to determine how UtAssert_GetOpText is invoked (what values are passed as CompareType). Even if the enum lists only the handled enumerators, callers may pass values outside the enum (casts, integers), so inspecting the caller(s) shows whether the default case can actually be reached at runtime and whether UtAssert_GetOpText itself is reachable from the program (global reachability).
